    <briefdescription>
<para>Type-safe handler for a specific command type. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1messaging_1_1command_1_1TypedCommandHandler" kindref="compound">TypedCommandHandler</ref> provides the interface for receiving commands of a specific type during the <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1messaging_1_1command_1_1TypedCommandBuffer" kindref="compound">TypedCommandBuffer</ref> flush. Managers that process commands implement this for each command type they handle.</para>
<para>A single Manager may implement multiple <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1messaging_1_1command_1_1TypedCommandHandler" kindref="compound">TypedCommandHandler</ref> specializations:</para>
<para>```cpp class SpawnManager : public Manager, public <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1messaging_1_1command_1_1TypedCommandHandler" kindref="compound">TypedCommandHandler&lt;SpawnCommand&gt;</ref>, public <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1messaging_1_1command_1_1TypedCommandHandler" kindref="compound">TypedCommandHandler&lt;DespawnCommand&gt;</ref> { bool submit(SpawnCommand cmd) noexcept override { ... } bool submit(DespawnCommand cmd) noexcept override { ... } }; ```</para>
<para>Handlers are registered with the ResourceRegistry during Manager::init() and looked up by the <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1messaging_1_1command_1_1TypedCommandBuffer" kindref="compound">TypedCommandBuffer</ref> at flush time.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>CommandType</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The command type this handler accepts.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
